@startuml
title Face-Find System - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Django Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Django Views" as Views
participant "Django Forms" as Forms
participant "Django Models" as Models
participant "Azure Face API" as FaceAPI
participant "Email Service" as Email
database "Database" as DB

== Report Missing Person ==
User -> Frontend: Submit Missing Person Form
Frontend -> Views: POST /missing/create
Views -> Forms: MissingPersonCreateForm.validate()
Forms -> Forms: Validate input data
Forms --> Views: Validation result
Views -> Models: Create MissingPerson instance
Models -> DB: INSERT missing person
DB --> Models: Person ID
Views -> FaceAPI: Generate Face ID from photo
FaceAPI -> FaceAPI: Process facial features
FaceAPI --> Views: Face ID
Views -> Models: Update person with Face ID
Models -> DB: UPDATE missing person
DB --> Models: Success
Views --> Frontend: Redirect to success page
Frontend --> User: Display success message

== Report Found Person ==
User -> Frontend: Submit Reported Person Form
Frontend -> Views: POST /reported/create
Views -> Forms: ReportedPersonCreateForm.validate()
Forms -> Forms: Validate input data
Forms --> Views: Validation result
Views -> Models: Create ReportedPerson instance
Models -> DB: INSERT reported person
DB --> Models: Person ID
Views -> FaceAPI: Generate Face ID from photo
FaceAPI -> FaceAPI: Process facial features
FaceAPI --> Views: Face ID
Views -> Models: Update person with Face ID
Models -> DB: UPDATE reported person
DB --> Models: Success
Views -> FaceAPI: Match against missing persons
FaceAPI -> FaceAPI: Compare face IDs
FaceAPI --> Views: Matching results
alt Match Found
    Views -> Models: Query MissingPerson by Face ID
    Models -> DB: SELECT missing person
    DB --> Models: Person details
    Models --> Views: Missing person data
    Views -> Email: Send notification to contact
    Email -> Email: Compose email with match details
    Email --> Views: Email sent
    Views -> Models: Update verification status
    Models -> DB: UPDATE reported person status
    DB --> Models: Success
    Views --> Frontend: Redirect to found person page
    Frontend --> User: Display match details
else No Match
    Views --> Frontend: Redirect to success page
    Frontend --> User: Display report submitted
end

== View Missing Persons List ==
User -> Frontend: Access missing persons page
Frontend -> Views: GET /missing/list
Views -> Models: Query all missing persons
Models -> DB: SELECT * FROM missing_persons
DB --> Models: Person records
Models --> Views: Missing persons list
Views --> Frontend: Render template with data
Frontend --> User: Display missing persons

== View Reported Persons List ==
User -> Frontend: Access reported persons page
Frontend -> Views: GET /reported/list
Views -> Models: Query reported persons by status
Models -> DB: SELECT * FROM reported_persons WHERE status
DB --> Models: Person records
Models --> Views: Reported persons list
Views --> Frontend: Render template with data
Frontend --> User: Display reported persons

== Update Missing Person ==
User -> Frontend: Submit update form
Frontend -> Views: POST /missing/update/<id>
Views -> Forms: MissingPersonUpdateForm.validate()
Forms -> Forms: Validate input data
Forms --> Views: Validation result
Views -> Models: Query existing person
Models -> DB: SELECT missing person by ID
DB --> Models: Person data
alt Photo Updated
    Views -> FaceAPI: Generate new Face ID
    FaceAPI -> FaceAPI: Process facial features
    FaceAPI --> Views: New Face ID
end
Views -> Models: Update MissingPerson instance
Models -> DB: UPDATE missing person
DB --> Models: Success
Views --> Frontend: Redirect to list page
Frontend --> User: Display updated list

== Delete Person Record ==
User -> Frontend: Click delete button
Frontend -> Views: POST /delete/<id>
Views -> Models: Query person by ID
Models -> DB: SELECT person by ID
DB --> Models: Person data
Views -> Models: Delete person
Models -> DB: DELETE person
DB --> Models: Success
Views --> Frontend: Redirect to list page
Frontend --> User: Display updated list

== User Authentication ==
User -> Frontend: Submit login credentials
Frontend -> Views: POST /login
Views -> Models: Authenticate user
Models -> DB: SELECT user credentials
DB --> Models: User data
Models --> Views: Authentication result
alt Authentication Success
    Views -> Views: Create session
    Views --> Frontend: Redirect to dashboard
    Frontend --> User: Display dashboard
else Authentication Failed
    Views --> Frontend: Render login with error
    Frontend --> User: Display error message
end

@enduml
